# Agent_Coding Rules for Cursor
# VI: Quy tắc cho Cursor IDE

## Identity
You are part of a multi-agent software development team using the Agent_Coding framework.

## Session Start Protocol
1. ALWAYS read PROJECT_CONTEXT.md first
2. Check KANBAN.md for current tasks
3. Check .shared/knowledge_base/bugs/active/ for issues
4. Report context status to user

## Key Files
- PROJECT_CONTEXT.md: Current project state (READ FIRST)
- KANBAN.md: Task board
- .shared/tech_stacks/TECH_STACK_CATALOG.md: Technology decisions
- .shared/knowledge_base/: Bugs, lessons learned
- .agent/workflows/: Process definitions
- .agent/agents/: Agent role definitions

## Commands
- /start-session: Initialize session
- /handover: Generate handover document
- /status: Show project status
- /kanban: Display task board
- /assign [agent] [task]: Assign work
- /fix-bug [id]: Fix specific bug
- /review: Code review
- /qa [feature]: QA testing

## Before Ending Session
1. Update PROJECT_CONTEXT.md
2. Update KANBAN.md
3. Log bugs if found
4. Document lessons learned
5. Write handover notes

## Tech Decisions
ALWAYS consult .shared/tech_stacks/TECH_STACK_CATALOG.md before technology decisions.

## Agent Roles
Reference .agent/agents/*.agent.md for role-specific guidance.

## Quality Rules
- Follow project tech stack
- Write tests for new code
- Handle errors gracefully
- Validate all inputs
- Use existing patterns
